    },
    "body": "The witness stack carries the public key and signatures for SegWit inputs (P2WPKH, P2SH-P2WPKH). Without access to it, kernel API callers cannot extract the sender key from these input types which is a requirement for silent payments scanning.\r\n\r\nAdds two functions to the C API:\r\n`btck_transaction_input_get_witness_stack_num_items` returns the item count\r\n`btck_transaction_input_get_witness_stack_item` serializes a single item by index through`btck_WriteBytes` callback, returning -1 if the index is out of bounds\r\n\r\nBoth are exposed on the C++ wrapper via `GetWitnessStackNumItems()`, `GetWitnessStackItem()`, and a `WitnessStack()` range method generated by `MAKE_RANGE_METHOD`",
